cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE

This paper is about a PyTorch-based open source framework for translation quality estimation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the implementation of winning systems of the WMT quality estimation campaigns, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and neural networks. This suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions benchmarking on datasets, which could involve computer vision techniques, leading to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of PyTorch suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be a relevant sub-category.
